China’s agriculture has undergone a series of improvements spanning land reforms and  agricultural cooperatives.Kenya must move beyond traditional one dimensional agriculture into a multifaceted enterprise driven by science and technology In 1963, Kenya’s Gross Domestic Product Per Capita was nearly one and half larger than that of China. Yet in just three decades ending in 2020, China lifted over 850 million people out of extreme poverty; becoming the first developing country to achieve the first of the UN's 17 Sustainable Development Goals. 



